To run this example you need to install FortranCL.

FortranCL is an OpenCL interface for Fortran 90. It allows programmers
to call OpenCL directly from Fortran. Kernels are still written in C.

More information and updated versions can be found in the FortranCL website:

http://code.google.com/p/fortrancl/

INSTALLATION
============

The basic download and installation procedure is to run:
(tested only on Apple Macbook Pro with Lion)

svn checkout http://fortrancl.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ fortrancl
cd fortrancl
autoreconf -i
./configure --prefix=/usr/local
make 
make install

Set FORTRANCL_ENABLED to ON in CMake and enjoy it
